Your production Repl is already connected to GitHub at github.com/leulgeb/ETOTCmembership on the main branch. That's perfect — we just need to connect your staging Repl to the same repo on a staging branch. Here's the complete setup:

Step 1 — Create the staging branch on GitHub
Go to github.com/leulgeb/ETOTCmembership
Click the branch selector (shows "main") → type staging → click "Create branch: staging from main"
Step 2 — Connect your staging Repl to GitHub
In your staging Repl, open the Shell and run these commands one at a time:

git remote add origin https://github.com/leulgeb/ETOTCmembership.git
git fetch origin
git checkout -b staging origin/staging
If it says "remote already exists", run this first:

git remote set-url origin https://github.com/leulgeb/ETOTCmembership.git
You'll be asked for your GitHub username and a Personal Access Token (not your password). To get a token:

Go to github.com → Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens → Tokens (classic)
Generate new token → check repo scope → copy it
Step 3 — Push staging changes to GitHub
Whenever you've tested something in staging and want to move it to production, run this in the staging Repl's shell:

git add .
git commit -m "describe what you tested"
git push origin staging
Step 4 — Merge staging → production via GitHub
Go to github.com/leulgeb/ETOTCmembership
Click "Compare & pull request" (appears after a push)
Set it to merge staging → main
Review the changes and click Merge
Step 5 — Pull to production (I do this for you)
After you merge on GitHub, just tell me "pull latest changes" here in the production Repl and I'll run:

git pull origin main
